      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly computed from the CFD solution and correspond to the clinically reported metric without intermediate surrogate transformations.",
      "rationale": "The quantity of interest — normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) — is directly computed from the CFD shear stress field using the Giersiepen power-law model. This QoI maps directly to the clinical acceptance metric. Required level 4 is met."
