    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factors falling below required levels, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification bounds remain below the absolute clinical hemolysis threshold at the 95th percentile. Residual gaps in software quality assurance, model form, and test sample adequacy are noted but deemed manageable under existing device surveillance commitments. Note: several factors were assessed without formally documenting the rationale for the required level in a structured acceptanceCriteria field, representing a process gap identified post-submission.",
